body:
Example code (minimised from some OpenSPARC code):
```
module add #(
	parameter N = 3
) (
	input [N-1:0] a, b,
	output [N-1:0] q
);
	assign q = a + b;
endmodule

module top(
	input [7:0] a, b,
	output [7:0] q
);
	add #8 add_i (.a(a), .b(b), .q(q));
endmodule
```

In Yosys this gives:
```
/home/david/ecp5/pp/pp.v:14: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected TOK_CONSTVAL, expecting '('
```

But other tools (LSE, Icarus & Verilator) seem to accept this.

